If you are unable to climb steps and wish to board a low-floor MAX car, wait mid-platform behind the white bumpy strip where you can be seen by the train operator. Ramps are located at the two doors in the center of the low-floor car. If the ramp is not extended by the MAX operator, push the blue button with the accessibility symbol located on either side of the door. The doors have to close before the ramp can deploy.
